1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 25=

3
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:49,333
You've been here a while?

4
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:55,920
Are you okay?

5
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:03,720
When a fat fish from the pond is thrown

6
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:04,680
on a chopping block,

7
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,040
it's bound to thrash around a bit.

8
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:09,880
It wouldn't be as tasty if it didn't.

9
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,000
Ling Yikai is exactly the same.

10
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:14,000
If he just surrendered,

11
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,520
I'd actually find it boring.

12
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:17,560
That's why I want him to fight back,

13
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:18,560
so I can crush him.

14
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:20,280
After all,

15
00:02:21,111 --> 00:02:22,680
he's suffering more than I am right now.

16
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,100
I'm just worried there'd be
trouble at the wedding.

17
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:27,120
Both families are here.

18
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,200
It'd be a mess.

19
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:29,720
I don't care.

20
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:33,360
My parents mean well,
and they don't hate me,

21
00:02:34,088 --> 00:02:36,120
but they never expected me
to have a good life.

22
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,440
But Ling Yikai finally

23
00:02:39,177 --> 00:02:40,840
became his
grandmother's pride and joy.

24
00:02:41,222 --> 00:02:42,880
He can't afford to mess this up now.

25
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:48,000
If my mom had been this ruthless

26
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,760
with my dad back then,

27
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,320
our family wouldn't
have ended up like this.

28
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,520
Your dad isn't like Ling Yikai.

29
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:57,040
Ling Yikai and I are the same type.

30
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,920
Neither of us

31
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,240
is willing to admit defeat.

32
00:03:00,755 --> 00:03:02,080
We just have to win a round.

33
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:04,160
If we keep losing,

34
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:05,760
we'll just keep playing.

35
00:03:08,111 --> 00:03:09,240
With you as my bridesmaid,

36
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:10,800
he lost another round.

37
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:12,480
It's fine by me.

38
00:03:12,955 --> 00:03:13,880
I don't care about him.

39
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,040
But he cares.

40
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,440
Inviting his first love

41
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,320
to be

42
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:20,680
my bridesmaid

43
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:23,400
is just a reminder

44
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,480
of how pathetic he is.

45
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:31,760
Three of Dots.

46
00:03:51,888 --> 00:03:54,000
(Zhao Lanxin: I've changed into my dress
and I'm getting my makeup done.)

47
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,920
(Everything is going like clockwork.)

48
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:56,288
(Have you had lunch?
Are you going out later?)

49
00:03:57,220 --> 00:04:00,220
(Gu Yan: No.)

50
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:01,900
(I have to work on my drafts.)

51
00:04:02,020 --> 00:04:07,100
(I haven't submitted the drafts
for either you or Lin Zhanqiao yet.)

52
00:04:07,711 --> 00:04:08,466
Five of Characters.

53
00:04:09,550 --> 00:04:10,733
Your lipstick is touched up.

54
00:04:10,740 --> 00:04:11,800
Anything else needs fixing?

55
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:12,440
All set?

56
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:14,440
Mom, Dad,

57
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,000
Ms. Lulu, and Mr. Wei,

58
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:17,920
stop after two more rounds.

59
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:19,222
I'll have the makeup artist

60
00:04:19,244 --> 00:04:20,200
do your hair and makeup.

61
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:21,760
No need. I'm good.

62
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,880
I put on new clothes today.

63
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:24,000
Everyone says I look sharp.

64
00:04:24,955 --> 00:04:26,000
I'm skipping makeup, too.

65
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:28,280
It's your wedding, not mine.

66
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,600
Just being here is enough.

67
00:04:29,933 --> 00:04:30,320
One Dot.

68
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,377
We don't need it either.

69
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:32,600
In that time,

70
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,600
we could play two rounds.

71
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,080
Lanxin,

72
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:37,120
your makeup looks so pretty today.

73
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:38,560
You really look like a bride.

74
00:04:39,177 --> 00:04:40,320
What are you talking about?

75
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:41,800
She is indeed the bride.

76
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,000
Honestly, Zhao Lanxin,

77
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:44,680
I've seriously

78
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:47,160
started to doubt
if you're even my daughter.

79
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,240
Who else's daughter would she be?

80
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:49,680
Tao.

81
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:51,422
Lanxin just has good luck.

82
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:52,600
It's just like playing Mahjong.

83
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,760
She's drawing the right tiles.

84
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,320
That's right.

85
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:55,840
Mom.

86
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,040
Just sit right here.

87
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,680
I'll have her do your hair here.

88
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,200
It won't interrupt the game.

89
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,000
You're my family.

90
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:03,360
You can't embarrass me in public.

91
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,120
No, we wouldn't do that.

92
00:05:05,711 --> 00:05:06,400
Keep playing.

93
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:07,600
My turn.

94
00:05:07,622 --> 00:05:08,422
Play your tile.

95
00:05:23,933 --> 00:05:25,088
Where's Zhao Lanxin?

96
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:26,600
In her parents' room.

97
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:29,240
She asked me to look after Grandma.

98
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:32,880
Grandma,

99
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:34,600
this is Zhou Mei.

100
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:35,977
Zhao Lanxin's good friend.

101
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:38,080
Thank you.

102
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,355
My pleasure.

103
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:40,600
Her voice...

104
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,640
She must be very pretty.

105
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:44,800
Grandma,

106
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:47,240
I actually knew Zhou Mei

107
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:48,560
long before I met Zhao Lanxin.

108
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:54,280
Grandma,

109
00:05:54,488 --> 00:05:55,577
let them do your hair.

110
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:56,760
I'll go to Zhou Mei.

111
00:05:56,844 --> 00:05:57,960
I'll be right back, okay?

112
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:58,600
Okay, okay.

113
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,680
What do you want?

114
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,640
How have you been?

115
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:14,880
That's not your concern right now.

116
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:17,422
I don't mean anything by it.

117
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:19,200
I just wanted

118
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,160
to know how you're doing.

119
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,080
No news is an answer.

120
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,480
I never thought

121
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,160
Zhao Lanxin and I

122
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,000
would end up like this.

123
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,560
Zhao Lanxin set this up

124
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,840
just to trap me.

125
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:43,200
If you fell

126
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:44,080
for this trap,

127
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,822
you obviously
wanted something out of it.

128
00:06:46,088 --> 00:06:46,760
Blame yourself.

129
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,120
I'm not blaming anyone.

130
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,840
I just want to tell you...

131
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:52,920
I like you.

132
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,200
It's always been you.

133
00:06:59,022 --> 00:07:00,080
I'm marrying Zhao Lanxin

134
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:01,120
for a lot of reasons,

135
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,600
but definitely not out of love.

136
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,320
I don't care.

137
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,360
Zhanqiao.

138
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:06,280
Congratulations.

139
00:08:06,955 --> 00:08:08,066
The dress is beautiful.

140
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:09,360
Thank you.

141
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:10,840
Regardless,

142
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:12,520
thanks for coming to my wedding.

143
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,280
A year ago,

144
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,480
everyone would have thought

145
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,960
you and He Han would marry first.

146
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:18,400
Nobody expected

147
00:08:18,466 --> 00:08:19,400
that I'd be the first

148
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,800
to tie the knot.

149
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:22,400
I came to your wedding

150
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:23,840
to make my stance clear.

151
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:27,720
You left Chenxing because of Ling Yikai.

152
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,840
It wasn't because we treated you poorly.

153
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,160
It's a big industry.

154
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,600
You don't have to
treat me like the enemy.

155
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:36,760
Focus on growing your own company

156
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,320
instead of trying to ruin Chenxing.

157
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,080
Lin Zhanqiao.

158
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:43,000
You've always been my benchmark.

159
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:45,480
Right now, I feel like

160
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,640
success means outdoing you.

161
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,960
You and He Han wanted to get married,

162
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,520
but you broke up.

163
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:54,600
I wanted to marry Ling Yikai,

164
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:55,600
and I did.

165
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:56,840
So, I beat you.

166
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,200
Or, for instance,

167
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:00,120
if the best new authors

168
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,720
choose to work with me

169
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:02,960
instead of you,

170
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:04,160
then I win again.

171
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:08,600
Don't even think about Gu Yan.

172
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,520
Let me work with Gu Yan,

173
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,480
and I'll give the other authors back.

174
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,360
He Han isn't doing well.

175
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:16,440
He needs you.

176
00:09:16,822 --> 00:09:17,840
Others might not know,

177
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,040
but I do.

178
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:20,160
He Han

179
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,560
is not Gu Yan.

180
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:22,840
They are not the same.

181
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:27,600
If you had to choose between them,

182
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:28,920
who would you pick?

183
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:35,800
For the wedding speech,

184
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,360
I hope you could do me a favor.

185
00:09:37,888 --> 00:09:38,960
I've already written it.

186
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,280
If you don't want to do it,

187
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:42,400
that's fine.

188
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,280
I can do this for you.

189
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:46,760
But since it's my blessing,

190
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,480
I will write it myself.

191
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:49,720
I need no help.

192
00:09:50,311 --> 00:09:52,022
The same goes for everything else.

193
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:07,111
(Project Proposal:
"Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui")

194
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:22,160
Hello?

195
00:10:22,333 --> 00:10:23,680
Hi, your food delivery is here.

196
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:24,920
I didn't order any.

197
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,720
Hi, your delivery.

198
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:43,480
I didn't order anything.

199
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:44,320
Look,

200
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:46,000
it has your number, so it's yours.

201
00:10:46,288 --> 00:10:47,760
Maybe someone ordered it for you.

202
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:49,488
Just take it.

203
00:11:01,860 --> 00:11:06,140
(Braised Sea Cucumber with Matsutake,
Steamed Grouper with Scallop Sauce)

204
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:18,220
(Zhao Lanxin: I ordered dinner for you.)

205
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:22,180
(Gu Yan: Why so much?)

206
00:11:22,288 --> 00:11:24,000
Mr. and Mrs. Zhao, we added a segment

207
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,080
(Zhao Lanxin: I'm having a feast,)
to the ceremony.

208
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,800
(so you should, too.)
We'll take a group photo on stage.

209
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:29,120
The two of you will stand by the bride.

210
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,840
The other two guests,

211
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:32,080
please stand by your partners.

212
00:11:32,090 --> 00:11:33,400
Stay in these positions for now.

213
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,320
Hold on.

214
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:36,400
This doesn't look right.

215
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:37,680
Ms. Lulu,

216
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:39,000
please swap places with Mr. Wei.

217
00:11:39,355 --> 00:11:40,280
- Switch places.
- Right.

218
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:40,990
That's much better.

219
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:41,320
Okay.

220
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:43,800
Groom.

221
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:45,577
Is your groomsman not here yet?

222
00:11:45,688 --> 00:11:46,644
I don't have one.

223
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:48,160
But what about the toasts?

224
00:11:48,311 --> 00:11:49,333
I'll handle it.

225
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:49,960
Understood.

226
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,080
Don't overdo it.

227
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,280
Grandma, let's head in.

228
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:53,960
Ms. Lin,

229
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:55,680
once they go in,

230
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:56,822
enter through the side door

231
00:11:56,866 --> 00:11:57,760
and wait by the stage.

232
00:11:58,040 --> 00:11:59,640
After the parents give their blessings,

233
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:00,511
it'll be your turn.

234
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:00,960
Okay?

235
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:01,960
Great. Let's begin.

236
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,760
Good evening, everyone.

237
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:13,800
Welcome to the wedding ceremony

238
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:16,480
of Mr. Ling Yikai

239
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:17,280
and Ms. Zhao Lanxin.

240
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:20,360
On behalf of the couple,

241
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:22,880
I'd like to express
our deepest gratitude.

242
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:23,800
Are you ready?

243
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,080
As the music starts,

244
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:28,560
the couple will walk
into a new chapter together.

245
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,400
At this moment,

246
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:48,480
they are the happiest
people in the world.

247
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:50,560
Surrounded by the light
of the chandelier,

248
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,840
and the roses and lilies,

249
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:55,080
they walk down this aisle of love

250
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:57,600
toward a lifetime of happiness.

251
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:14,600
Next, the couple will exchange rings.

252
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:15,480
Bridesmaid, please.

253
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:23,640
Your love burns as bright as fire,

254
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,280
nourishing each other's souls

255
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:28,040
and bringing warmth to every moment.

256
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:31,400
Today, the world celebrates with you.

257
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:34,720
Groom, you may now kiss your bride.

258
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:43,760
One should be grateful
to have found the one and only.

259
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:45,320
From now on,

260
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,360
I'll have one less single friend.

261
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,560
Love shouldn't
require exhausting effort.

262
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:50,960
Zhao Lanxin is married now.

263
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:53,440
But marriage only
ends your single status.

264
00:13:54,520 --> 00:13:55,600
It doesn't end solitude.

265
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,560
I actually really admire her.

266
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:03,480
I even envy her.

267
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:08,040
If I had her courage,

268
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,240
so many of my problems

269
00:14:11,644 --> 00:14:12,560
would've been solved.

270
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:18,760
No one can step

271
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,640
into two different rivers at once.

272
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:23,720
Once you take one path,

273
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:26,640
you're bound to miss

274
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,400
the view on the other.

275
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,600
So, where is the path you've chosen?

276
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:35,400
Witnessed by friends...

277
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,400
Love may have its moments

278
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:46,440
of competition

279
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:48,200
and keeping score.

280
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:49,160
However,

281
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:51,240
these two hearts are now one.

282
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,000
As they move forward,

283
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,320
their passion will remain.

284
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:56,080
In this very moment,

285
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,080
with him by her side,

286
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:58,480
the family in the audience,

287
00:14:58,720 --> 00:14:59,480
and their friends,

288
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:01,480
this beautiful scene

289
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:02,720
is preserved in time.

290
00:15:18,644 --> 00:15:19,800
Zhao Lanxin is so good to you.

291
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:20,920
She bought all this stuff.

292
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:22,600
Much nicer than Lin Zhanqiao.

293
00:15:24,133 --> 00:15:25,280
Even on her wedding day,

294
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,080
she made time for you.

295
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:29,600
She's only nice to people she can use.

296
00:15:31,444 --> 00:15:33,440
Lin Zhanqiao doesn't
know you're working for her?

297
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:38,800
She probably knows by now.

298
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:42,240
Pick one.

299
00:15:42,555 --> 00:15:43,177
So, which one?

300
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:50,320
Here's my analysis.

301
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:53,720
You like Lin Zhanqiao,

302
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:55,200
but she doesn't like you back.

303
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:57,520
You don't like Zhao Lanxin,

304
00:15:57,560 --> 00:15:59,520
but she truly cares about you.

305
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,640
I'd still choose Lin Zhanqiao.

306
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:03,760
But she breaks your heart.

307
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:05,840
Wang Hai.

308
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:08,800
Life was much harder for us growing up.

309
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:10,680
We've had enough heartbreak.

310
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:13,040
If we choose another person

311
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,520
who makes us miserable,

312
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:16,720
when we look back in our old age,

313
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,080
it'll just be all about the pain.

314
00:16:19,577 --> 00:16:21,560
That's just
too much suffering for one life.

315
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:23,680
Right?

316
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:33,880
You are the one

317
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:37,240
who broke my heart.

318
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,200
I'm sorry.

319
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:50,480
I'm with Er Jiu now.

320
00:16:52,822 --> 00:16:54,000
I'm telling you officially.

321
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:55,880
I'm going to marry him.

322
00:16:58,080 --> 00:16:58,840
At least he says

323
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,560
he'd do anything for me.

324
00:17:01,155 --> 00:17:02,280
He'll grow old with me.

325
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:07,120
Er...

326
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:09,400
Er Jiu? Where did he go?

327
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:10,720
You said

328
00:17:11,733 --> 00:17:13,240
you wanted to bring the food up.

329
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,080
I sent him out for a bit.

330
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:34,520
I want to be clear with you.

331
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:38,920
Once I've said this...

332
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:42,920
Wang Hai.

333
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:49,040
I can't love you anymore.

334
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,360
I'll hurt this one last time.

335
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,920
Then, no one will break my heart again.

336
00:18:17,733 --> 00:18:18,360
In the future,

337
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:21,320
if you and Er Jiu fight again,

338
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:22,720
I'll take his side.

339
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:30,880
If I have anything good,

340
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,040
I'll save it for him.

341
00:19:41,740 --> 00:19:52,180
(Tiangong Manor)

342
00:19:58,360 --> 00:19:59,840
Look who's actually on time.

343
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:01,280
I have time when I'm not writing.

344
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:02,040
What's this about?

345
00:20:03,080 --> 00:20:04,360
To buy you dinner.

346
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:05,960
I can afford my own dinner.

347
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:07,200
Are you serious?

348
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,040
Who else is coming?

349
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:10,600
An investor.

350
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:12,200
For whom?

351
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:14,480
He could be yours,

352
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:15,840
if you're interested.

353
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:18,720
Hurry, come on.

354
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:23,400
Mr. Du.

355
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:26,480
Mr. He Han! Mr. He Han!

356
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:28,400
It's finally an honor to meet you.

357
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:30,520
I'm truly privileged, Mr. He Han.

358
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:32,560
Please, Mr. He Han.

359
00:20:34,540 --> 00:20:36,500
(Du Cheng, Founder/CEO of Shanghai
Infinite Reading Technology)

360
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:37,120
Mr. He Han.

361
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:38,720
The title on this card

362
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:39,640
doesn't matter.

363
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:41,320
What matters is you.

364
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:42,440
I'm a reader of yours.

365
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:43,760
A huge fan.

366
00:20:43,933 --> 00:20:45,400
I've been looking forward to this.

367
00:20:45,640 --> 00:20:46,680
To be honest, Mr. He Han,

368
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:48,080
I started this platform

369
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:49,440
specifically for you.

370
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:51,600
Have you seen the subway ads lately?

371
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:53,280
In the tunnels?

372
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:54,560
The ads for the platform

373
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:55,600
are mine.

374
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,480
I can already see it.

375
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:58,960
On our next batch of posters,

376
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,800
we'll be using your photo.

377
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,200
Our slogan will be,

378
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:04,840
"He Han invites you to read."

379
00:21:07,377 --> 00:21:08,520
I haven't introduced them.

380
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:10,840
This is Mr. Du from Infinite Reading.

381
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:11,440
Mr. Du.

382
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:13,120
And his secretary, Shishu.

383
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:13,760
Excuse me?

384
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:15,160
Du Shishu.

385
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:17,644
Like being "scholarly."

386
00:21:21,911 --> 00:21:23,444
Excuse me, I'll be right back.

387
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,160
I'll go with him.

388
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:28,720
He Han.

389
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:30,360
He Han!

390
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:32,400
What is going on?

391
00:21:32,480 --> 00:21:33,720
What is Infinite Reading?

392
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:34,844
I've never heard of it.

393
00:21:34,866 --> 00:21:35,977
It's a new platform.

394
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:37,520
Does Mr. Du even read?

395
00:21:38,155 --> 00:21:39,866
He sees the potential in our industry.

396
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,720
You have a huge reputation.

397
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:45,080
Once word got out
that you and Mr. Fan had split,

398
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:48,200
every company
was desperate to work with you.

399
00:21:48,377 --> 00:21:49,040
And obviously,

400
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:51,920
Mr. Du was
the most generous with his offer.

401
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:55,960
Infinite Reading
is just getting started.

402
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:58,960
They want to use your name
to break into the market.

403
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:00,760
So,

404
00:22:01,280 --> 00:22:03,120
isn't that
a great position to negotiate?

405
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:05,080
Do they know
you're not my manager anymore?

406
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:06,000
Yes.

407
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:07,160
But so what?

408
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:09,600
That doesn't stop me
from introducing you.

409
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:11,840
How much are they paying you?

410
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:18,880
You know,

411
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:21,360
you need a fresh start.

412
00:22:22,160 --> 00:22:24,040
I'm doing this entirely for you.

413
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,920
I just want to look out for your future.

414
00:22:35,280 --> 00:22:35,840
Sit, please.

415
00:22:35,920 --> 00:22:36,840
Ms. Dai, come on in.

416
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:38,960
Mr. Du,

417
00:22:39,555 --> 00:22:41,520
I feel like
we've known each other forever.

418
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:44,280
So, before we drink,

419
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:45,480
I want to be honest with you.

420
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,520
I'm all ears. Go ahead.

421
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,280
I can't write anymore.

422
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,040
Wait, what do you mean?

423
00:22:53,760 --> 00:22:55,280
Mr. He, what are you...

424
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:57,480
I can't write novels anymore.

425
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:01,800
That's why the Dingqi
terminated my contract.

426
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:04,120
Mr. He is just joking.

427
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:05,000
I'm not.

428
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:16,844
That doesn't matter, Mr. He.

429
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:20,720
You're a novel platform,

430
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:22,080
and I'm a novelist.

431
00:23:22,280 --> 00:23:23,360
If I can't write,

432
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:24,520
how can we collaborate?

433
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:26,160
It really doesn't matter, Mr. He.

434
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:28,160
If you can't write, fine.

435
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:30,920
As long as
you've written before, it's fine.

436
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,200
Give us the rights

437
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:35,200
to your name

438
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:36,280
and your photo.

439
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:37,920
Then, we'll pick any novel,

440
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:38,822
give it a nice title,

441
00:23:39,120 --> 00:23:40,600
and start the preorders.

442
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:42,200
Take your time writing.

443
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:43,333
There's no rush at all.

444
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,560
Of course, we need a title

445
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:46,520
that's explosive.

446
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:46,840
Yes.

447
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:48,440
Like "The Man-Eating Flower on the Run."

448
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:50,680
Or "I Rule the World."

449
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:51,577
Titles like those.

450
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,840
You're a marketing genius, Mr. Du.

451
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,000
You flatter me, Mr. He.

452
00:23:55,720 --> 00:23:57,280
I know writing is exhausting.

453
00:23:57,440 --> 00:23:57,760
It is.

454
00:23:58,360 --> 00:23:59,240
All that creativity

455
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:00,760
will cause hair loss.

456
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:01,200
True.

457
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:04,080
You are the brand now.

458
00:24:04,511 --> 00:24:05,822
No need to write anymore.

459
00:24:06,088 --> 00:24:08,280
I'll monetize it for you, okay?

460
00:24:10,066 --> 00:24:11,288
What about Dai Shan?

461
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:14,040
Ms. Dai is now a shareholder

462
00:24:14,040 --> 00:24:15,640
of Infinite Reading.

463
00:24:20,533 --> 00:24:21,800
I need the restroom again.

464
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:22,160
Okay.

465
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:23,640
I think I ate something bad.

466
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:24,840
Take your time.

467
00:24:25,355 --> 00:24:26,360
I'll go check on him.

468
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:26,760
Sure.

469
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,240
You saw that, right?

470
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:31,440
I asked for his help

471
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,880
because he has passion, not just money.

472
00:24:33,960 --> 00:24:35,120
And he's willing to listen.

473
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:37,640
We can guide him onto the right track.

474
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:39,160
Don't all startups

475
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:41,160
go through a phase like this? We...

476
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:41,920
I...

477
00:24:42,133 --> 00:24:43,520
Don't invite me to dinner again.

478
00:24:55,900 --> 00:25:01,340
(Wedding)

479
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:30,840
You drank too much tonight.

480
00:26:50,866 --> 00:26:51,755
What's wrong?

481
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:53,400
Mrs. Bei wants to see me.

482
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:54,840
Why?

483
00:26:55,333 --> 00:26:56,000
She didn't say.

484
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:56,840
Just to chat.

485
00:26:57,320 --> 00:26:58,320
Does Lawyer Bei know?

486
00:26:59,155 --> 00:27:00,440
She told me not to tell him.

487
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:01,960
She also said

488
00:27:02,111 --> 00:27:03,266
I could pick the place.

489
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:05,120
I'll go with you.

490
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:06,120
No need.

491
00:27:06,977 --> 00:27:08,480
I doubt she's looking for trouble.

492
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:11,120
You should still stay on your guard.

493
00:27:12,088 --> 00:27:12,720
Don't worry.

494
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,880
You're finally back.

495
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:31,920
What's wrong now?

496
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:35,160
The forums say
Mr. He Han can't write anymore.

497
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:36,200
That he's dried up.

498
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:37,760
Look at this.

499
00:27:39,240 --> 00:27:40,600
What a load of rubbish.

500
00:27:41,040 --> 00:27:41,640
Come look.

501
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:44,400
Anyone could have writer's block,

502
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:45,040
but not He Han.

503
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:47,240
You're a fan and you don't believe him?

504
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:48,440
He said it himself.

505
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:51,080
He told the owner
of Infinite Reading in person.

506
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:53,040
Some old fans asked him that.

507
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:54,600
(Maybe family issues.)
He admitted it.

508
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:56,890
(No way! I don't believe it.)
He likely rejected an offer.

509
00:27:56,955 --> 00:27:59,311
(He Han replied to YYDS Qiong: Yes.)
It's just another excuse.

510
00:27:59,422 --> 00:28:01,111
Many companies are probably after him.

511
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:03,200
This way,
he keeps the distractions away.

512
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,600
Then, he can announce a comeback later.

513
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:06,280
Simple.

514
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:07,440
Right?

515
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:10,120
Exactly.

516
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:12,520
Ms. Lin,

517
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:15,080
is Mr. He Han really quitting?

518
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:16,680
Look,

519
00:28:16,680 --> 00:28:18,480
he hasn't mentioned any new projects.

520
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,400
There's no plan for the future.

521
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:22,160
Ms. Lin,

522
00:28:23,520 --> 00:28:25,640
it's okay
if Mr. He Han is just struggling.

523
00:28:25,640 --> 00:28:27,200
As long as he can recover.

524
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:31,120
I can accept that. I'll wait.

525
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,680
He won't stop writing.

526
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:35,560
How else would he make a living?

527
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:37,160
Besides,

528
00:28:37,760 --> 00:28:38,680
she won't abandon him.

529
00:28:59,060 --> 00:29:04,380
(He Han)

530
00:29:12,540 --> 00:29:16,100
(In this endless chaos, a secret
about the world's survival lies hidden.)

531
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:40,920
I think writing is just like talking.

532
00:29:41,560 --> 00:29:42,840
You'll always be able to write.

533
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,480
It's just a matter of

534
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:46,080
whether it's good or not.

535
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,160
If it's not great,

536
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:49,000
you can always

537
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:50,720
deliver something.

538
00:29:51,680 --> 00:29:53,440
I'd rather not write than write poorly.

539
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:55,560
This is your job.

540
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:58,080
If you don't work, you don't eat.

541
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:00,520
Your routine

542
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:01,600
is different from others.

543
00:30:02,080 --> 00:30:03,000
You work at night.

544
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:04,560
You tried bars

545
00:30:04,933 --> 00:30:06,000
but found them too loud.

546
00:30:06,560 --> 00:30:07,160
Otherwise,

547
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:08,600
you wouldn't be

548
00:30:08,760 --> 00:30:09,960
in my quiet little shop.

549
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:10,640
Right?

550
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:38,960
Jackpot.

551
00:30:50,620 --> 00:30:52,580
(Upload digital license. Submit info.)

552
00:30:52,580 --> 00:30:53,820
(Dida Ride-Hailing Driver Application)

553
00:30:53,820 --> 00:30:55,060
(Registration submitted.
Reviewing driver info...)

554
00:30:55,060 --> 00:30:56,380
(Review takes 3-7 days.
Results via SMS.)

555
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:58,080
Sir, we have every kind of model here.

556
00:30:58,200 --> 00:30:59,000
Take this one.

557
00:30:59,240 --> 00:30:59,840
It's German.

558
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:01,960
We also have Japanese cars,

559
00:31:02,280 --> 00:31:03,560
local Chinese brands,

560
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:05,040
and American cars, too.

561
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:06,440
Just let me know

562
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:08,040
your preferred color.

563
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:09,080
We have SUVs

564
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:10,520
and some of our

565
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,240
top-selling local brands.

566
00:31:12,320 --> 00:31:13,666
See if anything catches your eye.

567
00:31:13,955 --> 00:31:14,760
This one's good.

568
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:16,720
You have an excellent eye, Sir.

569
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:18,680
This gray Magotan

570
00:31:18,680 --> 00:31:20,360
is the newest version.

571
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:21,960
The owner barely drove it

572
00:31:22,066 --> 00:31:23,200
before being posted abroad.

573
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:24,640
If you're interested,

574
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:26,560
feel free to take it for a spin.

575
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:27,760
It's smooth.

576
00:31:31,240 --> 00:31:31,680
I'm back.

577
00:31:31,777 --> 00:31:32,540
Welcome back, Sir.

578
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:43,960
Why are you here?

579
00:31:45,244 --> 00:31:46,600
I'm not going back to Chenxing.

580
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:47,720
I've found a new job.

581
00:31:51,280 --> 00:31:52,600
What kind of new job?

582
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:56,120
What can you do besides write novels?

583
00:31:57,400 --> 00:31:58,920
I really don't want to fight anymore.

584
00:32:00,280 --> 00:32:01,800
I have plenty of options.

585
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:03,480
It's not like when we first met

586
00:32:03,480 --> 00:32:04,622
and I was just a writer.

587
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:06,200
I used to work in kitchens.

588
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:07,360
I know my way around a stove.

589
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:09,320
But you can't go back to that.

590
00:32:10,955 --> 00:32:12,600
Then, I'll drive for a ride-hailing app.

591
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:17,240
Are you serious?

592
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:20,240
I can drive the night shift.

593
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:21,440
Very few jobs

594
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:22,840
fit my schedule this perfectly.

595
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:31,040
I've already picked out a car.

596
00:32:31,280 --> 00:32:32,440
I can start after training.

597
00:32:38,440 --> 00:32:39,680
How much can you make a month?

598
00:32:40,360 --> 00:32:41,640
Enough for rent and food.

599
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:44,120
Why the sudden decision?

600
00:32:46,533 --> 00:32:47,840
Instead of sitting here all night

601
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:48,920
with nothing to show for it,

602
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:50,160
I'd rather get working.

603
00:32:50,160 --> 00:32:50,840
Don't you agree?

604
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:53,400
So I take it

605
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:56,240
you just need a temporary reset.

606
00:32:57,360 --> 00:32:58,920
But this can't be a long-term plan.

607
00:33:01,622 --> 00:33:03,266
How long do you plan to drive?

608
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:04,960
Who knows?

609
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:06,560
We'll see.

610
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:08,240
Maybe I'll end up liking it.

611
00:33:10,360 --> 00:33:11,120
And quit writing?

612
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:17,880
I'm done.

613
00:33:20,560 --> 00:33:22,120
The reviews, good or bad...

614
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:26,040
Bad endings, plagiarism,
being washed up...

615
00:33:26,040 --> 00:33:26,840
Who cares?

616
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,040
I don't care anymore.

617
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:31,480
I think it's time

618
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:34,280
to let everyone forget He Han.

619
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:37,960
Just like they forgot
Phantom Knight.

620
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:39,000
How can they forget?

621
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:40,240
By driving.

622
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:41,920
That's how I'll move on.

623
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:45,440
But for you...

624
00:33:48,840 --> 00:33:50,000
It means staying away from me.

625
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:58,800
Every time we meet,
it's just about novels.

626
00:33:58,960 --> 00:34:00,320
What else would we talk about?

627
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:01,000
Nothing.

628
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,560
We could talk about your new job.

629
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:03,680
I'd like to know.

630
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:06,200
What's there to say about ride-hailing?

631
00:34:18,640 --> 00:34:20,280
If you've decided to start over,

632
00:34:22,240 --> 00:34:23,840
you need to leave writing behind

633
00:34:23,840 --> 00:34:24,600
for good.

634
00:34:25,920 --> 00:34:27,320
Say goodbye to your past.

635
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:29,880
Good or bad,

636
00:34:31,640 --> 00:34:32,360
let it go.

637
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:34,320
No one

638
00:34:34,640 --> 00:34:36,560
can ever truly
walk away from their past.

639
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:38,200
Even if you're a driver now,

640
00:34:39,120 --> 00:34:39,760
you can't

641
00:34:39,760 --> 00:34:41,280
just become a man without a past.

642
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:46,960
You're still He Han.

643
00:34:53,160 --> 00:34:54,200
Just let me try.

644
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:04,680
In any case,

645
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:08,600
don't leave me in the dark.

646
00:35:12,520 --> 00:35:13,720
Even a phone call will do.

647
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:17,680
I can't call while driving at night.

648
00:35:17,800 --> 00:35:19,222
I'll be sleeping during the day.

649
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:21,960
I've driven before.

650
00:35:21,960 --> 00:35:23,200
You don't need to worry about me.

651
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:24,400
You told me to stop bothering you.

652
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:24,920
You were right.

653
00:35:24,920 --> 00:35:26,800
Just message me occasionally.

654
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:28,088
Let me know you're safe.

655
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:30,880
Let me know you're doing okay.

656
00:35:49,620 --> 00:35:52,870
♪My heart is beating still♪

657
00:35:53,910 --> 00:35:56,930
♪Sometimes I feel alone♪

658
00:35:57,610 --> 00:36:00,870
♪But love should not be frail♪

659
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:04,880
I do love you, Lin Zhanqiao.

660
00:36:05,300 --> 00:36:08,640
♪Is there a spell♪

661
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:10,200
I just hate myself more.

662
00:36:12,410 --> 00:36:16,070
♪That binds and lingers bare♪

663
00:36:18,890 --> 00:36:20,360
♪If there's a way♪

664
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:23,580
♪To save me from the blue♪

665
00:36:23,940 --> 00:36:27,860
(Year 2015)

666
00:36:34,480 --> 00:36:35,360
I sent it to you.

667
00:36:36,720 --> 00:36:37,920
It's 10,000 words.

668
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:39,800
It's finally done.

669
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:43,440
♪With all of my tears♪

670
00:36:43,440 --> 00:36:44,620
♪And past pain♪

671
00:36:44,620 --> 00:36:47,110
♪I will still try♪

672
00:36:50,460 --> 00:36:53,210
♪Please stay with me♪

673
00:36:53,240 --> 00:36:53,920
Stop hiding.

674
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:55,600
I saw it.

675
00:36:55,600 --> 00:36:57,900
♪I could've held you in my arms♪

676
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:01,030
♪When I said love♪

677
00:37:01,030 --> 00:37:03,750
♪Will hurt somehow♪

678
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:06,000
You've written 10,000 words today.

679
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:08,360
You can drink a little.

680
00:37:10,150 --> 00:37:13,160
♪If love is meant to come♪

681
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:13,920
Tired?

682
00:37:13,930 --> 00:37:18,150
♪Don't bind my soul♪

683
00:37:19,640 --> 00:37:20,640
Not with you around.

684
00:37:23,140 --> 00:37:27,780
(Jiajia Inn)

685
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:36,610
♪If there's a way♪

686
00:37:36,610 --> 00:37:41,560
♪To save me from the blue♪

687
00:37:42,490 --> 00:37:43,480
♪I guess♪

688
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:49,140
♪It's rising from my silence♪

689
00:37:50,290 --> 00:37:52,130
♪I'm only someone♪

690
00:37:52,130 --> 00:37:56,980
♪Trying to chase the clouds away♪

691
00:37:57,850 --> 00:37:59,510
♪With all of my tears♪

692
00:37:59,510 --> 00:38:00,810
♪And past pain♪

693
00:38:01,270 --> 00:38:02,890
♪I will still try♪

694
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:04,600
Hello.

695
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:06,840
Ending in 2286?

696
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:07,800
Hello.

697
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:10,760
Your private driver is at your service.

698
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:12,080
Your trip is about to begin.

699
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:13,320
Please fasten your seatbelt.

700
00:38:14,630 --> 00:38:17,210
♪When I said love♪

701
00:38:17,210 --> 00:38:19,360
♪Will hurt somehow♪

702
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:20,920
How long have you been a driver, Sir?

703
00:38:22,444 --> 00:38:23,280
About three years.

704
00:38:26,240 --> 00:38:26,920
It must be tough.

705
00:38:28,040 --> 00:38:28,640
It's a living.

706
00:38:28,755 --> 00:38:29,644
Everyone works hard.

707
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:33,720
What did you do before?

708
00:38:34,560 --> 00:38:35,000
Me?

709
00:38:36,288 --> 00:38:37,222
I owned a restaurant.

710
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:39,800
All set. Let's go.

711
00:38:41,020 --> 00:38:44,690
♪I could've held you in my arms♪

712
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:50,440
Ms. Lin.

713
00:38:50,555 --> 00:38:52,480
I've printed
Gu Yan's latest chapter for you.

714
00:38:55,760 --> 00:38:57,040
Are there any updates on Sansan's

715
00:38:57,080 --> 00:38:58,410
"Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui"?

716
00:38:58,520 --> 00:38:59,822
If so, print a copy for me, too.

717
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:00,760
Ms. Lin...

718
00:39:03,760 --> 00:39:04,560
Anything else?

719
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:09,560
Mr. He Han has left the fan forum.

720
00:39:11,640 --> 00:39:12,600
And word is

721
00:39:13,200 --> 00:39:14,840
he's going to be a ride-hailing driver.

722
00:39:15,320 --> 00:39:16,000
Did you know?

723
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:19,600
I didn't.

724
00:39:21,266 --> 00:39:23,240
But writers taking a break
to experience life

725
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:24,800
and clear their heads

726
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:27,600
is quite normal.

727
00:39:53,100 --> 00:39:57,020
(Year 2014)

728
00:40:14,740 --> 00:40:18,340
(Notepad)

729
00:40:54,500 --> 00:40:57,100
(Year 2014)

730
00:41:07,960 --> 00:41:08,360
Excuse me.

731
00:41:08,977 --> 00:41:10,560
Can you take a look? Can this be fixed?

732
00:41:11,320 --> 00:41:12,040
Can you at least

733
00:41:12,040 --> 00:41:13,200
help me recover the data?

734
00:41:13,688 --> 00:41:14,480
Is there a way?

735
00:41:20,750 --> 00:41:24,280
♪Because I see you there♪

736
00:41:28,220 --> 00:41:31,140
(Year 2015)

737
00:41:31,680 --> 00:41:32,080
I'm sorry.

738
00:41:37,660 --> 00:41:38,500
Hey! Hey!

739
00:41:38,680 --> 00:41:39,800
Give me back my phone!

740
00:41:40,640 --> 00:41:41,280
Don't run!

741
00:41:41,750 --> 00:41:46,950
♪Just to love and be with you♪

742
00:41:59,230 --> 00:42:02,550
♪Now I cross the line♪

743
00:42:04,020 --> 00:42:08,630
♪To be with you and love you♪

744
00:42:54,160 --> 00:42:54,960
With He Han gone,

745
00:42:55,160 --> 00:42:56,720
your position is unshakable.

746
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

747
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

748
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

749
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

750
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

751
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

752
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

753
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

754
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

755
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

756
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

757
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

758
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

759
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

760
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

761
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

762
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

763
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

764
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

765
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

766
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

767
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

768
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

769
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

770
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

771
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

772
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

773
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

774
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

775
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

776
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

777
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

778
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

779
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

780
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

781
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

782
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
